		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Pyramid scheme</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:352px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Pyramid_scheme.svg" class="image" title="The unsustainable geometric progression of a classic pyramid scheme"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Pyramid_scheme.svg/350px-Pyramid_scheme.svg.png" width="350" height="225" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Pyramid_scheme.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The unsustainable geometric progression of a classic pyramid scheme</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A <b>pyramid scheme</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Non-sustainable" title="Non-sustainable" class="mw-redirect">non-sustainable</a> <a href="/wiki/Business_model" title="Business model">business model</a> that involves the exchange of <a href="/wiki/Money" title="Money">money</a> primarily for enrolling other people into the scheme, often without any <a href="/wiki/Product_(business)" title="Product (business)">product</a> or <a href="/wiki/Service_(economics)" title="Service (economics)">service</a> being delivered.</p>
<p><a href="/wiki/Pyramid" title="Pyramid">Pyramid</a> schemes are illegal in many countries, including the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a><sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>, the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>, <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a>, <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a>, <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a>, <a href="/wiki/Romania" title="Romania">Romania</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Colombia" title="Colombia">Colombia</a><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Malaysia" title="Malaysia">Malaysia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Norway" title="Norway">Norway</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bulgaria" title="Bulgaria">Bulgaria</a>, <a href="/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australia</a><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/New_Zealand" title="New Zealand">New Zealand</a><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a><sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Italy" title="Italy">Italy</a><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6" title=""><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Nepal" title="Nepal">Nepal</a><sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since March 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Philippines" title="Philippines">Philippines</a><sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7" title=""><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</a><sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Sri_Lanka" title="Sri Lanka">Sri Lanka</a><sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Thailand" title="Thailand">Thailand</a><sup id="cite_ref-.E0.B8.AA.E0.B8.A1.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.84.E0.B8.A1.E0.B8.81.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.A3.E0.B8.82.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.A2.E0.B8.95.E0.B8.A3.E0.B8.87.E0.B9.84.E0.B8.97.E0.B8.A2_10-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-.E0.B8.AA.E0.B8.A1.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.84.E0.B8.A1.E0.B8.81.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.A3.E0.B8.82.E0.B8.B2.E0.B8.A2.E0.B8.95.E0.B8.A3.E0.B8.87.E0.B9.84.E0.B8.97.E0.B8.A2-10" title=""><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a><sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since March 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup>, and the <a href="/wiki/People%27s_Republic_of_China" title="People's Republic of China">People's Republic of China</a><sup id="cite_ref-Regulations_for_the_Prohibition_of_Pyramid_Sales_11-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Regulations_for_the_Prohibition_of_Pyramid_Sales-11" title=""><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup>. These types of schemes have existed for at least a century.</p>
